HEADWORD: Entoptic
<hw>Ent*op"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ent-</ets> +
<ets>optic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Relating to objects
situated within the eye; esp., relating to the perception of objects in
one's own eye.</def>⟦br⟧
